<typeStatus box="[549,588,1734,1753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
queen. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Schmidt and Shattuck" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Rasopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Rasopone breviscapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mackay and Mackay" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[257,382,1762,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Rasopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rupinicola">
<emphasis box="[257,382,1762,1781]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">R. rupinicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[439,526,1763,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Rasopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titanis">
<emphasis box="[439,526,1763,1781]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">R. titanis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the largest species in the genus, with HW ~1.7. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Schmidt and Shattuck" authorityYear="2014" box="[387,581,1792,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Rasopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapa">
<emphasis box="[387,581,1792,1811]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Rasopone breviscapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the anterior clypeal margin truncate, mandibles striate, and petiole intermediate between cuboidal and scale-like. It is differentiated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mackay and Mackay" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[649,770,1850,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Rasopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rupinicola">
<emphasis box="[649,770,1850,1869]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">R. rupinicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[153,217,1880,1899]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[146,173,1819,1836]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,149,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[184,1403,147,1783]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 13. Distribution map,face view,and lateral view of petiole of Rasopone cubitalis (holotype worker),R.titanis (worker,Mexico,Chiapas,MCZ-ENT00716640), R.breviscapa (holotype queen),and R.rupinicola (worker,Colombia,face view MCZ-ENT00716589,petiole CASENT0217567).On distribution maps,red dots are sites with UCE sequence data. Red boxes are type locality." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3826729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3826729/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
; Supp Figs. S30 and S31 [online only]) by the shorter scapes (SI 79 vs 106), and from 
<taxonomicName box="[387,473,1910,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Rasopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titanis">
<emphasis box="[387,473,1910,1928]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">R. titanis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[488,554,1909,1928]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[146,173,1819,1836]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,149,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[184,1403,147,1783]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 13. Distribution map,face view,and lateral view of petiole of Rasopone cubitalis (holotype worker),R.titanis (worker,Mexico,Chiapas,MCZ-ENT00716640), R.breviscapa (holotype queen),and R.rupinicola (worker,Colombia,face view MCZ-ENT00716589,petiole CASENT0217567).On distribution maps,red dots are sites with UCE sequence data. Red boxes are type locality." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3826729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3826729/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
